d with traditional golfers on the course. To make it easier on golfers, footgolf will start later in the day.\n\n‚ÄúWe purposefully positioned the timing of this to be after the more busy time of golfing in the morning,‚Äù Saputo said. ‚ÄúGolfers typically like to get on the course between 6:30 and 7 a.m. We pushed the weekday play of footgolf after 11 a.m. on purpose. It doesn‚Äôt mean the two can‚Äôt be played simultaneously, but we did want to be conscious and respectful of our traditional golfers and the game they like to play.‚Äù\n\nSince some footgolf participants may not be familiar with golf courses, the park district will be teaching players some basic golf etiquette so the interaction with traditional golfers goes as smooth as possible.\n\nWhile Bergen is a nine-hole golf course, there are 18 holes set up for footgolf. The distance from the tee area to the hole is staggered so that people with different skill levels can enjoy the game. The different tees are color-coded.\n\n‚ÄúThe blue tee is the farthest. It‚Äôs about 100 to 120 yards,‚Äù Saputo said. ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs about 70 yards kicking off from the red tee.‚Äù\n\nFaith‚Äôs previous soccer experience was a definite benefit, but the whole family was enjoying the game.\n\n‚ÄúShe‚Äôs much better at it than we are, but the whole family can do this,‚Äù said Faith‚Äôs dad, Brian Turley. ‚ÄúThe group we‚Äôre with is having a lot of fun. It‚Äôs a nice day out here and it‚Äôs good exercise walking the course.‚Äù\n\nLaquesha Russell of Springfield and her 12-year-old son were with the Turleys on the course.\n\n‚ÄúIt‚Äôs interesting. It‚Äôs fun for the children to get out, enjoy the weather and learn something new,‚Äù Russell said. ‚ÄúEverybody is enjoying themselves.‚Äù\n\n___\n\nSource: The (Springfield) State Journal-Register, http://bit.ly/2rtvBMh\n\n___\n\nInformation from: The State Journal-Register, http://www.sj-r.com	2017-06-26 11:38:33.983808+03	0	0	0	0	\N	\N	6	726	['The Washington Times Http', 'John Reynolds